6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to the Strong Readers Act; creating
the Oklahoma Reading Excellence through
8 Accountability, Development, and Standards (READS)
Act; amending 70 O.S. 2021, Section 1210.508C, as
9 last amended by Section 2, Chapter 297, O.S.L. 2025
(70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 1210.508C), which
10 relates to reading assessments; requiring a Student
Reading Proficiency Team to include certain coach, if
11 assigned; removing language allowing certain students
to demonstrate proficiency on certain screening
12 instruments; requiring retention of certain third-
grade students who do not meet certain grade-level
13 targets on certain statewide assessment and do not
qualify for certain exemption; directing certain
14 performance levels to ensure students are meeting
certain criteria; requiring school districts to
15 include certain information in annual report;
providing good-cause exemptions for promotion of
16 certain students; providing process for evaluation of
good-cause exemption requests; directing certain
17 intervention services to be provided to certain
students subject to retention; allowing a school
18 district to provide an intensive acceleration class
for retained third-grade students; requiring the
19 State Department of Education to employ literacy
coaches; providing qualifications for literacy coach;
20 providing for assignment and duties of literacy
coaches; updating statutory language; updating
21 statutory references; amending 70 O.S. 2021, Section
1210.508D, as amended by Section 6, Chapter 411,
22 O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 1210.508D),
which relates to Strong Readers Act funding;
23 directing allocation for certain retained students;
amending 70 O.S. 2021, Section 1210.508E, as amended
24 by Section 7, Chapter 411, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp.
Req. No. 14088 Page 1

1 2025, Section 1210.508E), which relates to summer
academies; updating statutory language; requiring,
2 rather than allowing, a teacher to recommend a summer
academy for students in certain grades; requiring
3 school districts beginning in certain summer to
provide a summer academy or other program to certain
4 students; requiring administration of certain
alternative assessment by certain date; providing for
5 promotion of students who attend certain academy or
other program; requiring school districts to notify
6 the State Department of Education by certain date
regarding offering of summer academy or other
7 program; providing for noncodification; providing an
effective date; and declaring an emergency.
