13 format to the State Department of Education, the Office of
14 Educational Quality and Accountability, and the Secretary of
15 Education the number of third-grade students retained pursuant to
16 this section, the number of third-grade students promoted to the
17 fourth grade due to a good-cause exemption as provided for in
18 subsection K of this section by each category of good cause, the
19 number of students in kindergarten through third grade per grade
20 level who exhibit grade-level reading proficiency, the number of
21 students per grade level who received intensive intervention
22 services pursuant to paragraph 2 of subsection F of this section,
23 the number of students per grade level who attended a summer academy
24 as provided for in Section 1210.508E of this title, the number of
Req. No. 14088 Page 11

1 stud ents per grade level who exhibited improved reading proficiency
